=========================================================
36. FUTURE
=========================================================

Represents result available later.

future.get();

Waits and returns result.

=========================================================
37. PROMISE
=========================================================

Used to pass value between threads.

std::promise<int> p;

std::future<int> f = p.get_future();

p.set_value(100);

=========================================================
38. PACKAGED_TASK
=========================================================

Wraps callable object.

Returns future result.

Less commonly asked.

=========================================================
39. THREAD POOL
=========================================================

Collection of worker threads.

Tasks assigned to workers.

Benefits:
- Reuse threads
- Better performance
- Avoid thread creation overhead

Frequently discussed in senior interviews.

=========================================================
40. THREAD SAFE
=========================================================

Code behaves correctly when multiple threads
access it simultaneously.

=========================================================
41. REENTRANT FUNCTION
=========================================================

Can be safely called simultaneously.

Uses no shared mutable state.

=========================================================
42. AVOIDING DATA RACES
=========================================================

- Mutex
- Atomic
